RELEASE NOTES

        
	SQL Query Inspector is a deadlock prevention tool for SQL Server 
	databases that analyzes the T-SQL code in the stored procedures,
	views, functions and triggers and reports instances of inconsistent
	table use. 

	Modules can be displayed in Notepad or cut and pasted to Query Analyzer
	or Management Studio. 

	SQI works with SQL Server versions 2000, 2005, and 2008 and can access
	databases on local and network servers.
